  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "CLOUD ARCHITECT",
  "description": "<p>•Lead the design of cloud-native architectures for complex, large-scale enterprise and digital-native workloads.</p><p>•Define reference architectures, reusable patterns, and best practices for multitier, microservices, and serverless applications.</p><p>•Conduct architecture reviews and provide recommendations for scalability, resilience, performance, and cost optimization.</p><p>•Partner with business stakeholders, solution architects, and engineering teams to align architectures with organizational goals and compliance standards.</p><p>•Building and deploying cloud-native applications using Java with the Spring Boot framework and related technologies.</p><p>•Architecting and implementing GitLab CI/CD pipelines for rapid, reliable delivery.</p><p>•Provisioning and managing AWS services such as EC2, ECS, EKS, Lambda, and ELB.</p><p>•Automating infrastructure provisioning with Infrastructure-as-Code (CloudFormation, Terraform).</p><p>•Troubleshooting and resolving complex issues across applications and infrastructure in both production and non-production environments.</p><p>•Work with CloudOps, DBA, Security, and application teams to deliver compliant and cost-optimized solutions.</p><p>•Support the CCoE in driving adoption of best practices and reusable frameworks across projects.</p><p>•Contribute to technical documentation, architectural diagrams, and knowledge sharing within the team.</p><p></p><p></p><p>Requirements</p><p>•10 years of experience in cloud architecture and engineering roles.</p><p>•Hands-on expertise with AWS core services (EC2, ECS, EKS, Lambda, ELB, VPC, IAM).</p><p>•Proficiency in Java with expertise in the Spring Boot framework.</p><p>•Solid understanding of container-based deployments, orchestration, and lifecycle management.</p><p>•Proficiency with scripting languages such as Python, Ansible, Bash, or PowerShell.</p><p>•Proven ability to design and implement scalable, resilient, and secure architectures.</p><p>•Strong knowledge of CI/CD and automation frameworks (GitLab, CloudFormation, Terraform).</p><p>•Working knowledge of cloud security, IAM, and encryption practices.</p><p>•Strong troubleshooting, problem-solving, and performance tuning skills.</p><p>•Excellent communication skills with the ability to engage executives, architects, and developers.</p><p></p>",
